        <scopecontent id="ref7">
            <head>Scope and Content</head>
            <p>The 
                <persname>Bill Thomson Papers</persname> consist of sketches, finished artwork, models, advertising artwork, and artwork created during Thomson's student days as well as documenting his life as a professional illustrator. There are also five panels documenting the creative process in the life of a brochure.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <arrangement id="ref8">
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>The Papers are arranged in two series, with Series I containing the bulk of the collection in seven boxes generally arranged by book project. Series II consists of the works of art in Art Storage.</p>
            <p>
                <emph render="bold">Series I: Preliminary and Finished Artwork, Photographs, Research Materials</emph> (
                <date> 1979-2010</date>)</p>
            <p>
                <emph render="bold">Series II: Exhibit panels and paintings</emph> (
                <date>undated</date>)</p>
        </arrangement>
